This paper focuses on designing and evaluating a two-factor authentication system on multi-touch mobile devices. The paper discusses the security and usability of the proposed system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the system involves user interaction with the touchscreen, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of behavioral and physiological characteristics for authentication, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The system involves drawing on the touchscreen, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper evaluates the system on Android devices, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
